snippet.textDisplay:
Why does everyone think climate change is all about greenhouse gasses? That's only a small part of it. The bigger cause of climate change is deforestation and the elimination of plants as we take up more and more land, then we also cover bodies of water with floating plastic and crap that prevents the water cycle from working properly.

Imagine how much less water can evaporate because we trap them in containers, in our trash, bury it underground, fracking, etc. Imagine a radiator that you restricted the flow of coolant or decreased the surface area by shrinking the radiator.

Plants are basically smart radiators for the planet. They help keep the planet cool with evaporative cooling, shade, and by pulling the water up from the ground so it can evaporate easier for rain to prevent drought. They feed us and provide housing for other animals. They take in CO2, the greenhouse gas, and put out oxygen. As it gets cooler, they drop their leaves to allow the sunlight to reach further, but at the same time the leaves act as insulation to the planet and keep the water from evaporating, basically like putting a lid on a pot. People need to do better studies on that and stop pushing just CO2 emission reduction, but to find ways to relocate plants that we remove so that we don't lose all the benefits they provide.

Imagine how much less water can evaporate because we trap them in containers, in our trash, bury it underground, fracking, etc. Imagine a radiator that you restricted the flow of coolant or decreased the surface area by shrinking the radiator.

Plants are basically smart radiators for the planet. They help keep the planet cool with evaporative cooling, shade, and by pulling the water up from the ground so it can evaporate easier for rain to prevent drought. They feed us and provide housing for other animals. They take in CO2, the greenhouse gas, and put out oxygen. As it gets cooler, they drop their leaves to allow the sunlight to reach further, but at the same time the leaves act as insulation to the planet and keep the water from evaporating, basically like putting a lid on a pot. People need to do better studies on that and stop pushing just CO2 emission reduction, but to find ways to relocate plants that we remove so that we don't lose all the benefits they provide.
